{!<div class="event-layout"><div class="event-portrait-col">Zentrum-chan<img class="event-portrait-img" src="img/portraits/Z_Full.png"></div><div class="event-dialogue-col">!}

Zentrum-chan politely waited for me after the end of class , and she doesn't waste any time bringing up the hottest subject to talk about.

Z: "So, SPD-chan are the rumors I've heard true?"

- @d1: "What rumors would that be?"

@d1

Z: "Don't tell me you don't know. I don't keep up with much gossip, and I have even heard about it."

I sigh. Of course, I knew. After DDP-Chan and I confessed to one another in the park, and we were walking through town to get something to drink, She gave me what she called her first gift to me: a sweet kiss on the lips that marked the official start of our relationship. But it turned out that our little public display of affection had been spotted by the DNVP, and a day later the rumor mill was working overtime spreading the news throughout the hallways of the school.

- @d2: "What have you heard?"

@d2

Z: "About the DDP kissing someone in the middle of the street..."


- @d3: "Guilty as charged. Is that enough for you?"

@d3

Zentrum-chan giggled and smirked.


Z: "I bet I'm not the first one to bother you about this, am I?"


- @d4: "More like the fifth. Which isn't too bad. Given the fact that the entire school seems to know about it, I was prepared for an interrogation by the DVP."

@d4

As we leave the classroom, we walk to the courtyard and take a few sips from our water bottles. We sit down for a moment, and Zentrum-chan starts to carefully adjust her necklace:


Z: "The rumor isn't really about you, you know. I mean, you're just an average socialist. But DDP-chan has been the shyest girl in school for the better part of four years, and a bourgeois party as well. It's no surprise people talk about something like this."


- @d5: "It's surprising, so many people seem to know her, given the effort she usually makes to avoid drawing attention to herself."

@d5

Z: "I don't think anyone except you and DVP-san really know her. But I bet most students know who she is. Sometimes, when you try hard enough to avoid being noticed, you end up standing out all the more."
"How did she react to the attention?"


- @d6: "She hates it. What did you expect? Before, she merely thought the others were staring at her all the time. Now, she KNOWS people are staring. She's been ditching the last few minutes of every class so far in an attempt to avoid DVP-san, and she's even taken off her favorite hair clip to pass as her sister"

@d6

Zentrum-chan looks down for a moment as she hears this, and gives me a sad smile.


Z: "That's too bad. I get that she hates people staring, but I don't think this kind of attention is a bad thing. It's a shame she can't enjoy it."

- @d7

@d7
